detaileddescription.para: List of aliases to destroy when this node disappears. FIXME: clarify usage and RW lock need.

Value that holds type information on the 'trigger' method of this object. If the type_ is not a list, this means the object is not callable and the type_ member only holds a string with general information on the object. If the type_ is a list, the first element is the actual type of Value the object can receive in it's 'trigger' method and the other elements are information on the range of allowed values and such. The last element of type_ is always an information string. FIXME: clarify usage and RW lock need.

Identifier for the type of the values the element can receive. The value is a hash of the type tag list (multiple osc type tags) such as "f" (single Real) or "fss" (Real, String, String). This is cached from the first element in type_. FIXME: clarify usage and RW lock need.
Root object used to access application methods/
Pointer to parent object. Can be NULL if the object does not have a parent.
Hash with pointers to children objects or methods. The children objects unregister themselves when they die or change their parent by calling 'unregister_child'.
List of children as a vector for faster enumeration type of access.
Unique name in parent's context.

========================== REPLIES TO META METHODS ====================== The replies to meta methods are implemented as virtuals so that objects that inherit from osc::Object just need to overwrite these in order to return more meaningful information / content. List sub-nodes. This method is used as a reply to the /.list meta method. The format of the reply is a list of names with the type: [name, name, ...].

List sub-nodes with their current value and type. This method is used as a reply to the /.list_with_type meta method. The format of the reply is a list of names with the type: [name, current, unit, ...], [name, current, unit, ...], etc.

List full tree under this node.
base_length
is the length of the url for the initial call (removed from results).
tree
returned value.
Human readable information method. Called as a response to "/.info '/this/url'".

Type information with current value (used to automatically generate the correct control). Called during response to "/.type '/this/url'".
